==English==

===Etymology===
Contraction of [[spastic]] (as a term of abuse)

===Noun===
'''spack'''

# {{cattag|slang|pejoratives}} a clumsy, foolish, or mentally deficient person
#:*"You spilt beer on your shirt, you '''spack'''!" 
#:*"'''Spack''' off!"  by Doctor Who in 1974's ''Genesis Of The Daleks''

====Usage notes====
Especially popular among English schoolchildren during the 1990s. Often considered taboo because of its origin.

====Derived terms====
* [[spack attack]] &mdash; a sudden outbreak of clumsy behaviour.

====Related terms====
* [[spacko]]
* [[spacka]]
* [[spacker]]
* [[spaz]]
* [[spastic]]

